19
00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:55.280
and rank the wrong candidate first

20
00:00:56.040 --> 00:00:58.900
Methane's carbon-hydrogen bond is brutally strong

21
00:00:59.800 --> 00:01:01.860
A catalyst active enough to crack it often

22
00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:05.040
holds the methanol product too tightly and over-oxidizes

23
00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:06.400
it into carbon dioxide

24
00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:10.040
Corrected barriers can expose rare sites that break

25
00:01:10.040 --> 00:01:13.200
this trap and open lower-temperature methanol or cleaner

26
00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:14.140
hydrogen routes

27
00:01:15.140 --> 00:01:17.720
Refrigerants face a different-looking version of the same

28
00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:18.160
problem

29
00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:21.560
Millions of molecules must be screened for vapor

30
00:01:21.560 --> 00:01:26.540
pressure efficiency flammability toxicity and atmospheric lifetime

31
00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:30.660
The safety-critical steps involve radicals and breaking bonds

32
00:01:31.060 --> 00:01:34.851
the same low-coordination physics that raw models misread

33
00:01:34.851 --> 00:01:38.240
Lupine measures the error versus atomic coordination anchors

34
00:01:38.240 --> 00:01:40.920
a correction field and applies it at runtime

35
00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:42.800
without retraining the base model

36
00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:46.760
Then machine-checked proofs mark which predictions stay inside

37
00:01:46.760 --> 00:01:47.680
